body:
@AudriusButkevicius I was going to file a PR but I am not sure on how to proceed. I could implement it in either of two ways:

My first idea was creating a default theme that imports the appropriate theme depending on a media query, something like:
```css
@import "path/to/white/theme.css" (prefers-color-scheme: light);
@import "path/to/dark/theme.css" (prefers-color-scheme: dark);
```
I think that would require changing the way assets are served since there is no way to access an asset outside of the current theme folder. The advantage of this setup is that the default theme doesn't need separate maintenance, it just links to the existing themes.

The second way of doing it is just creating a new CSS default file by adapting the white/dark theme files. This would require no changes to the server code but it would entail maintaining separately a new file. 

Which way do you think would be best? Is any of these what you had in mind?
